Press Releases.Title: 31 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection (21 Sep)
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 21 September 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 31 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore. Based on our investigations so far, there are no cases in the community.

2.            There are 9 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. 

3.            We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
21 SEPTEMBER 2020
